Harry HACKWORTH, Appellant, v. A. C. ADERHOLD, Warden, United States Penitentiary, Atlanta, Georgia, Appellee. No. 7583. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Oct. 31, 1935.

Before FOSTER, SIBLEY, and WALKER, Circuit Judges.

Harry Hackworth, in pro. per. Lawrence S. Camp, U. S. Atty., Harvey H. Tisinger, Asst. U. S. Atty., and H. T. Nichols, Sp. Atty. to U. S. Atty., all of Atlanta, Ga., for appellee. PER CURIAM.

The judgment is affirmed.
